  exerciseTitle: Switch State Enum
  exerciseText: Do a switch on the State enum and run the correct function for each
    state.
  hintText: Remember the switch syntax, handle all the cases and call the functions.
  solutionText: "switch (state) {\r\n    case State.Idle:\r\n        HandleIdle();\r\n       
    break;\r\n    case State.LookingForEnemy:\r\n        HandleLookingForEnemy();\r\n       
    break;\r\n    case State.MovingToEnemy:\r\n        HandleMovingToEnemy();\r\n       
    break;\r\n    case State.AttackingEnemy:\r\n        HandleAttackingEnemy();\r\n       
    break;\r\n}"
  completedText: Here you learned how to make a super basic state machine, just do
    a switch on an enum state and run the logic for that state.
